{"word":"αἰσχύνω","slug":"αἰσχύνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>αἰσχύνω</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ s.\">s.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ prec.\">prec.</a> <el>αἰσχ-</el>entries; the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ act.\">act.</a>, which is not used in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ NT\">NT</a> = ‘disfigure, cause shame to’] only in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ mid.\">mid.</a> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pass.\">pass.</a> in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ NT\">NT</a><b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> ‘to have a feeling of shame’, <b><i>be ashamed</i></b><i></i> <b><a href='B:490 16:3'>Lk 16:3</a>; <a href='B:670 3:16'>1 Pt 3:16</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a>; <a href='B:670 4:16'>4:16</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> ‘to experience shaming’, <b><i>be put to shame, be disgraced</i> <a href='B:570 1:20'>Phil 1:20</a>; <a href='B:540 10:8'>2 Cor 10:8</a>.</b> In <b><a href='B:690 2:28'>1 J 2:28</a></b> the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ prep.\">prep.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀπό\">ἀπό</a></el> may emphasize a sense of separation <i>shrink from... in shame</i> (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Mft.\">Mft.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ transl.\">transl.</a>). <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:αἰσχύνη\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:αἰτέω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}